As a byproduct of fixing the missing-entry bug in write committed + two_write_queues + WBWI ingest, write committed transactions running with two_write_queues=true now share the same behavior as write prepared and write unprepared: a compaction filter's FilterMergeOperand will not be invoked on merge operands at or below the latest published sequence number. Write committed with a single write queue is unaffected.
